<HEADLINE>
US says Pakistan must sort out political problems
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON 2008-08-14 15:10:21 UTC
</P>
<P>
The United States says the struggles of Pakistan's new government
are an internal political matter that Pakistan's leaders must
sort out for themselves.
</P>
<P>
U.S. ally President Pervez Musharraf is being pushed to quit by
rivals and could face an impeachment motion as early as next
week. Musharraf called in a speech Thursday for reconciliation
and political stability.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman Robert Wood told reporters Thursday
that Pakistan has been a good partner in the fight against
extremists but could do more.
</P>
<P>
He says U.S. officials want to "make sure that we're all giving
100 percent effort in the war against terror." He says U.S.
officials have regular talks with Pakistani officials about ways
to improve efforts to fight extremists.
</P>
